    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey i'm working on a research paper and i think i keep using passive voice too much. can u help me identify it and show me how to fix it? like if i have a sentence like \"the data was collected by the researchers\" how do i make it better?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The passive voice can be a sneaky thing, but don't worry, I'm here to help you identify and fix it. You're on the right track by recognizing the sentence you provided. In this case, \"the data was collected by the researchers\" can be rephrased to \"the researchers collected the data\" or \"The researchers are responsible for collecting the data.\" This change makes the sentence more active and engaging, don't you think? It's a bit like a brave warrior, taking charge and doing the deed themselves, rather than just being the recipient of someone else's action.",
